<HEADLINE>
WHY HERB CAEN WORE A HAT  
 
 
 &HT;     BY SCOTT OSTLER 
</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
Deep thoughts, cheap shots, bon mots ...
<P>
   _ They are majestic, soaring creatures, sure, but the Union
Square pigeons now lurk about in alarming numbers. I saw one
wearing a tiny sign: ``Will peck for food.''
</P>
<P>
   We should at least cash in. Give 'em an exotic name and export
'em. Or at least bag and sell their byproduct as 'Frisco
Fertilizer.
</P>
<P>
   _ Janet Reno is going to bat for environmentalists and for the
Cuban kid, but the big question is: Where does she eat in S.F.?
</P>
<P>
   On her recent visit: Straits Cafe, Geary at Parker. Singaporean
cuisine. Janet dined with two friends, and brought another three
carloads of Secret Service agents.
</P>
<P>
   Four cars, no problemo. Who's going to tow the Atty. Gen.'s
rides?
</P>
<P>
   _ Moose's legendary bartender Bobby McCambridge told my man on
the street, Manny Street, ``I'm going in next week for the
triple.''
</P>
<P>
   Rasped Manny, ``Hospital or Santa Anita?''
</P>
<P>
   _ Like history? Opening Friday at Stanford: Martin Luther King
exhibit, ``The Unfinished Dream.'' Rare &AMP; important photos,
documents. A letter from Malcolm X to MLK; a letter written by
11-year-old King to his parents. Cypress Hall D. (650-725-8828).
</P>
<P>
   &LR; COL. 1 of OSTLER14 (106678 ) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &LR;  _ You're an old-timer if you remember salted peanuts on airlines.
Them was the days. Now you get a ``Party Mix,'' but it's good to
know they've found a way to recycle the snack-cracker-factory
sweepings. One step up from kitty litter.
</P>
<P>
   _ Sparky update: Old Sparky (Florida's electric chair) _
sentenced to death. Sparky Anderson (former manager) _ good bet for
Hall of Fame. Sparky Schulz (Peanuts cartoonist) _ five more
Sundays, and thanks for the memories. (Sigh!)
</P>
<P>
   _ Monica's next pitch for Jenny Craig: ``I was so big, I could
barely fit under a desk.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Covering all bases: During a recent NFL game telecast, a
public-service announcement on child abuse was immediately followed
by a promo for ``Family Feud.''
</P>
<P>
   _ The smoke-breakers in the parking structure at Marathon Plaza
on 2nd Street, claims Doug Wilkins, are mostly employees of the 24
Hour Fitness center. Hey: Buns of steel, lungs of phlegm.
</P>
<P>
   _ Chet Helms, recently declared dead, wants to know where he can
register for funeral gifts. My suggestion: Bed, Bath &AMP; Beyond.
</P>
<P>
   _ Found: Colony of Grinches. In Tampa, a neighborhood
association demanded the dismantling of a tree house of a
10-year-old kid dying of leukemia. Now neighbors, under pressure,
say tree house can stay ``as long as it's a medical necessity.''
</P>
<P>
   &LR; COL. 2 of OSTLER14 (106678 ) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &LR;  But the second the kid kicks, that eyesore's gotta go, capice?
</P>
<P>
   _ Add airlines: Why are they withholding information that would
help Americans diet away zillions of pounds? Do the right thing,
airlines: Release the secret plans to your machine that extracts
the taste from food.
</P>
<P>
   _ Prediction: Mondo haul for native son Carlos Santana at the
Grammys. The goodwill he's built up over the years in the music biz
will be repaid in hardware.
</P>
<P>
   Telegram from Quincy Jones to Santana when the 10 nominations
rolled in: ``I felt like it was happening to me.''
</P>
<P>
   This will help, too: The CD kills.
</P>
<P>
   _ Hillary Clinton, asked by Dave Letterman what we should do
about the Cuban kid: ``We need to do what's best for the child.''
</P>
<P>
   If you're like me, you slapped your forehead and exclaimed,
``Why hasn't anybody thought of that?''
</P>
<P>
   _ Wonder if Hillary ever said that about Monica?
</P>
<P>
   _ Hillary's next Top Ten list: ``The 10 baseball teams that are
No. 1 in my heart.''
</P>
<P>
   _ What the Rev. Robert Cromey says to those Noe Valley folks who
object to the shelter for young gays proposed for their collective
back yard: ``We landlords and homeowners have made a bundle in real
estate. We forced the rents sky high and thus are part of creating
homeless youth. ... I am now ashamed to be part of the
neighborhood.''
</P>
<P>
   &LR; COL. 3 of OSTLER14 (106678 ) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &LR;  _ Las Vegas is planning three S.F.-theme casinos. Cuffs Corbett
suggests we sell 'em some surplus landmarks.
</P>
<P>
   Candlestick Park, we won't need that much longer. The Bay
Bridge, once the new one is built in 2073. Treasure Island, which
is just dirt and would ship easily.
</P>
<P>
   Says Cuffs, instead of bringing a casino to Treasure Island, as
Willie Brown once suggested, bring Treasure Island to a casino.
</P>
<P>
   Also: Alcatraz, because Las Vegas could use a classy debtors'
prison.
</P>
<P>
   _ And let's send Vegas Union Square's feathered Luftwaffe.
</P>
