   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ Using American Online to connect
to the Internet is like riding a race bike with training wheels.
AOL is slick, pretty, touchy-feely and in the way, in my opinion.
My opinion doesn't count because AOL just pulled off the biggest
merger in history when it plunked down $165 billion to buy Time
Warner. (Rowland Nethaway is senior editor of the Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED
