<P>
   SCIENCE/MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   COXNET SCIHEALTH PAGE
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This is the CoxNet SCIHEALTH page for the current week.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET SCIHEALTH 0111 -- Just who should put patients to sleep
before surgery _ doctors who are anesthesiologists or nurse
anesthetists _ has become a war in the operating room. (Nesmith,
Cox News Service) Art includes 3-column color photo of a
anesthesiologist.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: HEALTH &AMP; MEDIA -- An interview with Dr. Judith Reichman,
author of ``Relax, This Won't Hurt: Painless Answers to Women's
Most Pressing Health Needs.'' (Guthrie, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) Art includes two color photos of her books.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: BONE MARROW -- Ten years after her bone marrow transplant,
an Ohio woman exults in life, despite her pain. (Lamb, Dayton Daily
News) Art includes 2-column color photo of woman wrapping a gift.
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION-SNAPSHOT _ In any 24-hour period: 55 percent of
Americans prayed at a meal; 36 percent read the Bible; 15 percent
attended a prayer service, Bible study or worship group; 5 percent
called a psychic hotline or read a horoscope. The Princeton
Religion Research Center offers snapshots from ``24 Hours in the
