<P>
   US-MIDEAST _ WASHINGTON _ Momentum builds this week on President
Clinton's crusade to broker a comprehensive Mideast peace accord
before leaving office in a year. Clinton will host Israeli Prime
Minister Ehud Barak and Syrian Foreign Minister Farouk Sharaa for a
second round of negotiations beginning Wednesday; the next day
Palestinian Authority President Yasser Arafat comes to town, amid
talk of a Barak-Arafat peace summit under White House auspices in
the weeks ahead. (Deans, Cox News Service) EDs: Moving Fri., Jan.
14, in both International/Washington categories.
</P>
