<P>
   FINANCE-HOOKER (Undated) _ Investor with a conservative
portfolio can't expect a lot of growth over a three-year period. He
would need 12.2 percent a year earnings to deliver $36,000 a year
without invading principal. By Kenneth Hooker.
</P>
