Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   LEND-LEASE _ ATLANTA _ Lend Lease (formerly Equitable Real
Estate), the nation's largest adviser to pension funds, has named a
California pension fund adviser as its new CEO. The former CEO had
his office in New York, but she will move to Atlanta, giving new
emphasis to the company's presence here. (Wilbert, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   RETAIL _ Advancer on National Retail Federation convention in
New York next week. (Degross, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MLK-COKE _ATLANTA _King family's ''Salute to Excellence'' honors
Doug Ivester, former Coke CEO, who was at the helm when black
employees sued for discrimination and who demoted the highest
ranking black executive in the company. Well, the King family is
not exactlyhonoring Ivester, representatives, say. Long ago they
decided to honor Coke at the turn of the millennium because of its
long term support of the King Center and civil rights. (Suggs,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
