<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Saturday, Jan. 15. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
STADIUM (Phoenix) - Arizona's Governor's Task Force is scheduled to
issue a final recommendation on funding for a new stadium for the
Arizona Cardinals, without choosing a site. The panel wants the
Cardinals to kick in $75 million, the Fiesta Bowl $20 million.
Public input would be from a half-percent bed tax statewide and
full percent in Maricopa County, plus a 3 percent Maricopa County
rental-car tax and a tax on players' income generated in the state.
We'll seek Legislative react. By PAT FLANNERY. Stor will move in
the ``A'' and ``S'' categories. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MIAFUNERAL (Washington) - Coverage of the funeral for Phoenix MIA
whose fate was unknown for 30 years. By JEFF BARKER. Story will
move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
SMART (Phoenix) - Futurists have long predicted the thinking
toaster. It turns out that the first thinking, talking kitchen
appliance will be the electric mixer. It can measure your flour,
double your cookie recipe and add butter to your shopping list if
you run out. And it can talk to your smoke detector, alarm clock or
electric blanket. Sunbeam will unveil a line of smart appliances
next week that are due to be on store shelves this year. By JON
SIDENER. Story will move in the ``L'' category. &QL; 
