   WALMART-APPOINT (Undated) _ David Glass, who aggressively
expanded Wal-Mart Stores Inc. from a rural discounter into a
worldwide powerhouse during his 12-year tenure as chief executive
and president, announced Friday that he would step down
immediately. As expected, he will be succeeded by his long-trusted
lieutenant and chief operating officer, H. Lee Scott. By Leslie
Kaufman.
</P>
