<DOCNO> NYT20000114.0277 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-14 20:37 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6546 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r e BC-TV-LORETTA-CLAIBORNE-     01-14 0301
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TV-LORETTA-CLAIBORNE-REVIEW-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
RACING PAST ADVERSITY WITH `THE LORETTA CLAIBORNE STORY'
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Eds: EMBARGOED until Sunday, Jan. 16; in this story, tonight is
Sunday. Fact box below) 
Our rating: 3 stars 
 
 
By DAVID KRONKE 
c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Tonight's ``Wonderful World of Disney'' offering, ``The Loretta
Claiborne Story,'' is pretty solid as inspirational TV movies go.
Kimberly Elise (``Beloved'') stars as Loretta, who was born mildly
retarded and with other physical setbacks that prevented her from
walking or talking until she was 4 years old. She surmounted her
disabilities, not to mention prejudice, to become both a
gold-medal-winning athlete at _ and a passionate spokesperson for _
the International Special Olympics. In 1996 she won the Arthur Ashe
Award for Courage.
</P>
<P>
   The Special Olympics couldn't have asked for a better calling
card. Elise gives a strong, tough, laudably unromanticized
performance, and she's matched the conviction Tina Lifford brings
to the role of Loretta's hard-working, over-extended single mom.
Emmy winner Camryn Manheim of ``The Practice'' makes something
interesting of the usually rote role of the angelic social worker
who believed in Loretta when no one else would.
</P>
<P>
   Director Lee Grant and screenwriter Grace McKeaney trust their
material and eschew manipulatively treacly moments; they've created
a smart and moving tribute to Claiborne and those like her, whose
fierce resolve overcomes their shortcomings. &QL; 
____ &QL; 
The show: ``The Wonderful World of Disney: The Loretta Claiborne
Story.'' &QL; 
What: Inspirational drama about a disabled girl who becomes a
champion athlete. &QL; 
The stars: Kimberly Elise, Camryn Manhein. &QL; 
Where: ABC. &QL; 
When: 7 tonight. &QL; 
Our rating: 3 stars &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
