<HEADLINE>
GET CLOSE TO THE CIA
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Eds: EMBARGOED until Sunday, Jan. 16; in this story, tonight is
Sunday. Fact box below) 
Our rating: 3 stars 
 
 
By DAVID KRONKE 
c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``On the Inside: The CIA'' is, by definition, a partial
whitewash, but it's still fascinating for its portrait of the most
secure _ and likely most paranoid _ organization in the world. How
secure/paranoid? Well, the CIA buildings in Langley, Va., are
surrounded by shell buildings, exo-skeletons, if you will; white
noise is pumped between the inner and the outer buildings so that
no listening devices may discern certain incriminating keystroke
patterns on the computer keyboards inside. If that's not intense
enough for you, try this: The guys dealing with the trash have the
highest security clearances imaginable.
</P>
<P>
   The report, narrated by James Coburn, portentously declares,
``Never before _ and never again _ will anyone delve so deeply''
into the agency's secrets. It's separated, arbitrarily, into two
one-hour parts: ``America's Front Line,'' relating fascinating
agency particulars, and ``The New Threats,'' touching on
international terrorism but getting bogged down in drug
trafficking. There's a lot of padding and rhetoric here,
particularly involving the recruiting techniques _ they seek out
the most qualified candidates for positions, who'da thunk? _ but
the dribbles of cool spy information make the dull stuff
worthwhile.
</P>
<P>
   In particular, a re-enactment of the painstaking detail that
went into a Panamanian prison rescue _ OK'd by former President
George Bush, one of the interviewees here, and lasting in its
actual execution a mere six minutes _ is utterly absorbing, alone
worth the price of admission, as they say. This is as close to CIA
headquarters as we're likely to get, and as close as most of us
probably would ever want. &QL; 
____ &QL; 
The show: ``On the Inside: The CIA.'' &QL; 
What: Documentary about the covert intelligence agency's operations
and paranoia. &QL; 
Where: Discovery Channel. &QL; 
When: 8 tonight; also Jan. 17, 23, 26 and 29. &QL; 
Our rating: 3 stars &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
